<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="814" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 EW/9–3044: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Huddle</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-06">December 6,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>4126. Please request the Swiss Government at its discretion as to manner and
                        timing to press the German Government to investigate the matter protested in
                        Department’s 3604 of October 23, 1944, and to take appropriate disciplinary
                        and penal action against persons responsible for the abuses referred
                            to.<note n="59" xml:id="d814fn59">Telegram 8438, December 30, 1944, from
                            Bern, reported that the Department’s communication had been delivered to
                            the German Foreign Office by the Swiss Legation in Berlin on December 19
                            (740.00116 European War/12–3044).</note>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>